## Executive Summary

The honeypot recorded **97,000 total attack events** across a 24-hour observation window, sourced from 10+ countries and spanning 10 distinct honeypot sensors. The volume and variety of activity confirm active, automated scanning at internet scale. Three distinct threat clusters stand out: a coordinated campaign targeting **AI/ML tooling ports** (Gradio, ComfyUI, TensorBoard) sourced exclusively from US-based IPs on a known abuse-tolerant hosting provider; a sustained **VoIP toll fraud scanning operation** generating 22k SIP probe events from German and US infrastructure; and continuous **SSH credential stuffing** via commodity botnets generating 23k Cowrie events throughout the full observation window.

The most operationally significant finding is the AI/ML port targeting - ports 7860, 8188, and 6006 collectively drew over 32,000 hits, representing an emerging and underappreciated attack surface. Any organisation running exposed Gradio or ComfyUI instances is at material risk.

